english:
  title: On the Last Day of the Third Month
  author: Seol Son
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Barley grows green and wheat stands tall in rows,
    Willow catkins fall like snow, sparse apricot blooms.
    A bird on the wind brushes past a wanderer,
    A solitary cloud above the horizon learns to fly like geese.

    The clear sky tempts me nearly to intoxication,
    Yet I fear spring will vanish in a moment.
    Silken saddles and jade bridles crowd the road,
    But lonely at dusk, I return alone, my song the only companion.
